1
00:00:09,583 --> 00:00:11,721
Pinocchio

2
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:45,310
Mother. Where are you right now?

3
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:49,736
Sir.

4
00:00:50,848 --> 00:00:52,239
Oh, Ms Choi.

5
00:00:52,330 --> 00:00:54,390
Why are you back already?
Why aren't you at your assigned post?

6
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:56,780
I'm sorry.
I have something important to do.

7
00:00:57,115 --> 00:00:58,415
Do you know where the Chief is perhaps?

8
00:00:59,021 --> 00:00:59,983
She's in the meeting room.

9
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:05,246
What's wrong with her?

10
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:12,422
-Were you this low, Chief?
-What are you doing at this hour?

11
00:01:12,513 --> 00:01:14,210
The cell phone
that you were looking for...

12
00:01:14,310 --> 00:01:16,170
I restored all the deleted messages.

13
00:01:16,270 --> 00:01:17,517
Try to explain to me what these are.

14
00:01:20,980 --> 00:01:23,740
It's been 13 years...
No, it's been 14 years already.

15
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:28,079
I thought that you might've misunderstood
the situation because of the media.

16
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:31,465
I thought that you did it
because of your own conviction.

17
00:01:32,797 --> 00:01:34,120
But was it like this?

18
00:01:34,923 --> 00:01:37,440
Were you someone who just writes down
whatever the Chairwoman orders?

19
00:01:37,550 --> 00:01:38,694
Are you sure...

20
00:01:40,135 --> 00:01:41,343
you're a real reporter?

21
00:01:50,660 --> 00:01:53,330
-How did you get this?
-Please explain.

22
00:01:53,869 --> 00:01:56,260
The texts that you sent to Ms Song...

23
00:01:56,731 --> 00:01:59,440
Telling her to use fireman Ki Ho-sang...

24
00:02:00,050 --> 00:02:01,267
What does this mean?

25
00:02:06,901 --> 00:02:08,172
Tell me you're not.

26
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,374
Tell me that you're not this scary.

27
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:14,740
Tell me that you're not
this horrible please.

28
00:02:15,288 --> 00:02:17,359
Who else knows about this other than you?

29
00:02:24,487 --> 00:02:27,673
-Did you really do this, mother?
-I said who else knows about this?

30
00:02:28,084 --> 00:02:29,790
What if someone else knows?

31
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,420
Just why did you do this?

32
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,750
Either explain it to me
or at least make excuses.

33
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,420
I told you before right?

34
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,645
I'll tell you
when you quit being a reporter.

35
00:02:47,749 --> 00:02:49,838
Captain. This is Seo Bum-Jo.

36
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:53,030
Starting today...

37
00:02:53,809 --> 00:02:55,496
I'm quitting MSC.

38
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:03,296
Is that good?

39
00:03:04,453 --> 00:03:06,358
I think I'm qualified to listen
to you answer.

40
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:19,983
Episode 17 - The Scarlet Letter

41
00:03:20,353 --> 00:03:21,540
That's right.

42
00:03:21,798 --> 00:03:23,413
I did send all these texts.

43
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:25,869
Because of that incident at that time.

44
00:03:27,617 --> 00:03:30,890
The Assemblyman that was looking after
my business was in a difficult situation.

45
00:03:31,067 --> 00:03:34,477
Issues with the plant
and the chemical disposal business...

46
00:03:34,577 --> 00:03:36,468
He was looking after all of them.

47
00:03:38,117 --> 00:03:41,753
But he was in a sensitive time
because of his by-elections...

48
00:03:42,137 --> 00:03:43,607
So...

49
00:03:44,267 --> 00:03:47,167
You framed fireman Ki Ho-sang
to cover that person?

50
00:03:47,277 --> 00:03:51,817
We just had to divert the attention
until the election was over.

51
00:03:51,917 --> 00:03:56,117
But I didn't even know
that the matter would get that big.

52
00:03:58,228 --> 00:04:02,409
If you consider everything,
what I did wasn't exactly illegal.

53
00:04:02,831 --> 00:04:06,801
I just did a small favor for someone
who was helping my business.

54
00:04:07,227 --> 00:04:09,982
This business is the same as farming.

55
00:04:10,147 --> 00:04:12,936
Things don't just grow
because you planted the seeds.

56
00:04:13,387 --> 00:04:16,117
You have to grow them
while getting your hands dirty

57
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,211
with smelly fertilizer and pesticides

58
00:04:18,307 --> 00:04:20,432
until you can finally hold the fruit
with your hands.

59
00:04:20,847 --> 00:04:23,457
Next month, I'll have the grand opening
at the Duty Free shop

60
00:04:23,557 --> 00:04:26,547
and the new shopping mall permit
in Yeonjoo.

61
00:04:26,677 --> 00:04:28,921
They're all businesses worth
several hundred million dollars.

62
00:04:29,201 --> 00:04:31,937
Those are all the farms
that I worked hard on for 20 years

63
00:04:32,037 --> 00:04:35,197
while I fertilized and nurtured.

64
00:04:35,307 --> 00:04:37,277
I just have to harvest now,

65
00:04:37,368 --> 00:04:40,740
but it keeps getting infested with bugs
so I'm really about to get irritated.

66
00:04:43,107 --> 00:04:44,707
What if...

67
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:47,681
What if these texts
are revealed to the world?

68
00:04:48,971 --> 00:04:51,201
Well, I'm sure we'll get criticized a bit.

69
00:04:52,017 --> 00:04:54,537
But it's already been 14 years.

70
00:04:54,637 --> 00:04:56,977
There's no law to apply
and even if there is one...

71
00:04:57,077 --> 00:04:59,517
the statutes of limitation must be over.

72
00:04:59,617 --> 00:05:01,257
I don't think
there's going to be any problems.

73
00:05:07,422 --> 00:05:09,817
By granting these kinds of favors...

74
00:05:10,277 --> 00:05:12,452
what did you gain for yourself?

75
00:05:13,392 --> 00:05:15,451
All the things that
you've been enjoying until now.

76
00:05:15,987 --> 00:05:17,217
And...

77
00:05:17,617 --> 00:05:20,337
And all the things
that you'll enjoy in the future.

78
00:05:30,047 --> 00:05:32,157
I just thought that you made a mistake
as a reporter.

79
00:05:32,807 --> 00:05:36,147
That you and Bum-jo's mom
were simply friends.

80
00:05:36,247 --> 00:05:37,537
No.

81
00:05:38,727 --> 00:05:40,322
I wanted to believe that.

82
00:05:42,257 --> 00:05:44,967
But how could you do such a thing?

83
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:48,015
As a reporter... No. How could you do
such a thing as a human being?

84
00:05:48,787 --> 00:05:50,377
Where...

85
00:05:50,987 --> 00:05:52,336
Where did you get that?

86
00:05:55,504 --> 00:05:57,515
You told me to argue with proof,
didn't you?

87
00:05:58,321 --> 00:06:00,830
I don't think there will be
any definite proof than this.

88
00:06:01,087 --> 00:06:04,467
Please answer me.
Just why did you do such a horrible thing?

89
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:07,470
-Lower your voice. Don't make a fuss.
-No.

90
00:06:08,071 --> 00:06:09,370
I am going to make a fuss.

91
00:06:09,997 --> 00:06:11,777
What Bum-jo's mother and you, mom...

92
00:06:12,217 --> 00:06:14,148
no, Chief, have committed...

93
00:06:14,337 --> 00:06:16,516
The atrocity you have committed...

94
00:06:16,919 --> 00:06:19,207
I'm going to report it no matter what.

95
00:06:19,307 --> 00:06:21,291
I'm going to reveal it
to the world in detail!

96
00:06:23,418 --> 00:06:24,845
I will reveal them all.

97
00:06:26,554 --> 00:06:27,389
February, 2000

98
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:30,367
Now that I'm aware of the truth,
I can't keep my mouth shut as a reporter.

99
00:06:30,619 --> 00:06:34,287
I'll report everything on the connection
between the Chairwoman and Chief.

100
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:37,255
Do you think that I will let you do that?

101
00:06:37,907 --> 00:06:39,851
Do you think that's possible?

102
00:06:40,677 --> 00:06:43,866
No. I'm sure it will be impossible at MSC.

103
00:06:44,257 --> 00:06:46,740
The report will go out from YGN.

104
00:06:47,629 --> 00:06:48,567
What?

105
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:51,127
I think that it's only right to report it
no matter what.

106
00:06:51,929 --> 00:06:55,477
So I decided to give
all the proof and files to YGN.

107
00:06:55,577 --> 00:06:57,289
Are you saying
you're going to be a whistle-blower?

108
00:06:58,457 --> 00:07:03,537
Are you aware of the consequences
of your action?

109
00:07:05,147 --> 00:07:07,927
I am prepared, to some degree.

110
00:07:08,027 --> 00:07:11,026
You won't be a reporter ever again.

111
00:07:11,677 --> 00:07:15,193
I'm curious to see
if you're prepared to that degree.

112
00:07:19,607 --> 00:07:22,447
Do you think that
you have the strength to report this?

113
00:07:22,547 --> 00:07:25,546
There's no way
this will be reported at MSC.

114
00:07:25,767 --> 00:07:26,907
I know.

115
00:07:27,007 --> 00:07:29,718
-The report will be given at YGN...
-So you'll be a whistle-blower...

116
00:07:31,227 --> 00:07:35,195
Are you aware that once you become
a whistle-blower, you'll be fired?

117
00:07:35,717 --> 00:07:37,152
I'm not afraid.

118
00:07:37,896 --> 00:07:40,747
The company where I can't say what I want
and has dirty connections...

119
00:07:41,054 --> 00:07:42,518
I'm not sorry to let it go.

120
00:07:42,737 --> 00:07:46,217
I'm going to start over
as a reporter at a proper company.

121
00:07:46,317 --> 00:07:49,350
Do you think you'll be able
to be a reporter again?

122
00:07:49,441 --> 00:07:50,281
Yes.

123
00:07:52,018 --> 00:07:55,083
Who will hire someone
who has been branded as a whistle-blower?

124
00:07:55,547 --> 00:07:58,267
What organization will welcome someone
who tattles

125
00:07:58,377 --> 00:07:59,744
about the internal problems to the world?

126
00:08:00,337 --> 00:08:02,327
There aren't any companies
in the world...

127
00:08:02,758 --> 00:08:03,917
that are that innocent...

128
00:08:05,577 --> 00:08:08,398
and righteous.

129
00:08:14,495 --> 00:08:15,877
14 years ago...

130
00:08:18,132 --> 00:08:19,681
I was exactly like you.

131
00:08:20,677 --> 00:08:21,699
Think about it very carefully.

132
00:08:22,427 --> 00:08:25,071
You just have to change your choice.

133
00:08:25,397 --> 00:08:29,426
If you cover this up,
I can have you gain more power.

134
00:08:29,863 --> 00:08:33,880
I can bring you up a position
where you will have a greater voice.

135
00:08:38,177 --> 00:08:39,637
For example...

136
00:08:39,737 --> 00:08:44,096
you can be the first woman captain
in the press.

137
00:08:46,344 --> 00:08:47,716
Opportunities like that...

138
00:08:50,606 --> 00:08:53,482
That decision brought me where I am.

139
00:08:55,645 --> 00:08:57,350
Of course, it's possible for you
to make a different choice.

140
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,380
You can give up being a reporter

141
00:08:59,597 --> 00:09:02,487
and live as a part-timer
at a convenience store.

142
00:09:02,597 --> 00:09:04,272
Following your conscience and purely...

143
00:09:05,717 --> 00:09:07,187
Now...

144
00:09:08,517 --> 00:09:10,957
you're almost done with the internship.

145
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:13,488
Don't you want to be a full-time employee?

146
00:09:14,077 --> 00:09:15,960
-Ms Song!
-Think about it.

147
00:09:16,637 --> 00:09:17,837
Just once...

148
00:09:18,457 --> 00:09:19,932
you can speak about one thing they want...

149
00:09:20,890 --> 00:09:24,567
and then speak about 99 right things.

150
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:26,097
Or...

151
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:30,838
a powerless person
who doesn't have a voice in the world.

152
00:09:37,106 --> 00:09:40,398
I don't want you
to become a powerless person.

153
00:09:40,813 --> 00:09:42,201
I'm telling you this not as a Chief...

154
00:09:46,525 --> 00:09:47,885
but as your mom.

155
00:09:53,202 --> 00:09:55,642
I saw how someone can be destroyed...

156
00:09:56,784 --> 00:09:58,286
when they become a whistle-blower.

157
00:10:00,452 --> 00:10:01,507
Who?

158
00:10:01,617 --> 00:10:02,666
Your father.

159
00:10:07,155 --> 00:10:09,287
You probably don't remember
because you were young.

160
00:10:10,117 --> 00:10:11,457
But your father...

161
00:10:12,217 --> 00:10:14,576
he was a pretty successful manager
at a bank.

162
00:10:15,129 --> 00:10:17,807
But he found out
about the president's illegal loans...

163
00:10:17,917 --> 00:10:20,818
and got fired
after reporting it to the newspaper.

164
00:10:22,917 --> 00:10:24,057
What do you think?

165
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:26,747
From what you can see...

166
00:10:26,847 --> 00:10:28,814
which is more pathetic,
between your father's life and mine?

167
00:10:33,301 --> 00:10:36,862
I've never thought
that dad's life was pathetic.

168
00:10:37,247 --> 00:10:39,906
If that's the consequence
of telling the truth, I'm rather proud.

169
00:10:41,848 --> 00:10:44,417
I'm going to make
a different choice than you.

170
00:10:59,927 --> 00:11:03,029
That bastard.
How could he date some other girl so soon?

171
00:11:06,857 --> 00:11:08,047
Hello?

172
00:11:08,427 --> 00:11:10,306
Can you come see me briefly?

173
00:11:16,257 --> 00:11:18,179
-I'm here.
-Are you bragging about being tall?

174
00:11:19,037 --> 00:11:20,111
If you came, sit down.

175
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,328
Your face looks good.

176
00:11:26,907 --> 00:11:27,914
Did something good happen?

177
00:11:29,227 --> 00:11:32,162
There's nothing special going on.

178
00:11:32,621 --> 00:11:35,344
Does In-ha know that you got another girl?

179
00:11:35,637 --> 00:11:36,907
Excuse me?

180
00:11:37,007 --> 00:11:38,548
What do you mean another girl?

181
00:11:39,011 --> 00:11:41,407
I saw it when I went
to your house recently.

182
00:11:41,507 --> 00:11:44,147
There was a long strand of woman's hair
in your room.

183
00:11:44,247 --> 00:11:46,297
Even if you're in a hot-blooded age,

184
00:11:46,407 --> 00:11:48,232
how could you bring another girl
to your room?

185
00:11:48,547 --> 00:11:50,267
A strand of woman's hair?

186
00:11:51,087 --> 00:11:52,927
-That's...
-Or...

187
00:11:53,037 --> 00:11:55,607
Are you going to tell me
that it's a guy friend with long hair?

188
00:11:55,707 --> 00:11:58,487
How can your heart be that shallow?

189
00:11:58,847 --> 00:12:02,397
How can you change your heart so easily

190
00:12:02,507 --> 00:12:04,012
when you liked In-ha
for such a long time?

191
00:12:05,257 --> 00:12:07,359
That was In-ha's.

192
00:12:08,407 --> 00:12:10,917
-What?
-In-ha came to my house that day.

193
00:12:11,017 --> 00:12:13,407
-It's not some other woman's.
-Really?

194
00:12:13,507 --> 00:12:15,447
That's what happened?

195
00:12:15,547 --> 00:12:19,287
I just thought perhaps...

196
00:12:22,847 --> 00:12:24,616
That was In-ha's?

197
00:12:28,737 --> 00:12:31,487
The more I think about it,
the more disgraceful I think it is.

198
00:12:31,577 --> 00:12:35,327
How could In-ha go in and out
to a guy's room like that?

199
00:12:37,217 --> 00:12:38,257
Dad.

200
00:12:38,357 --> 00:12:41,809
-Where are you, dad?
-You brat. I got you now.

201
00:12:43,367 --> 00:12:46,857
-Dad, I have something to ask you.
-I'm the one with something to ask you.

202
00:12:46,957 --> 00:12:49,577
I heard it from Dal-Po that
you went to his house before, right?

203
00:12:49,677 --> 00:12:52,207
Although you guys grew up
as uncle and niece,

204
00:12:52,307 --> 00:12:53,984
he's still a guy.

205
00:12:54,387 --> 00:12:57,938
I never thought
that your life was pathetic.

206
00:12:58,197 --> 00:13:00,498
If that's the consequence
of telling the truth, I'm rather proud.

207
00:13:04,917 --> 00:13:06,118
Why are you looking at me like that?

208
00:13:07,017 --> 00:13:07,943
It doesn't feel good.

209
00:13:08,597 --> 00:13:10,677
No. It's nothing.

210
00:13:11,037 --> 00:13:12,277
What did you want to ask me?

211
00:13:12,377 --> 00:13:15,137
I'm not going to ask you.

212
00:13:16,227 --> 00:13:17,998
In-ha! In-ha!

213
00:13:31,927 --> 00:13:33,267
Are they crazy?

214
00:13:33,358 --> 00:13:35,541
Who do they think they are
to manipulate the public opinion?

215
00:13:37,207 --> 00:13:40,280
This is NTS, isn't it?
This is clearly NTS from what I can see.

216
00:13:40,751 --> 00:13:42,867
Captain. Don't try to stop me.

217
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:45,717
-I'm going to expose them all.
-You stand aside.

218
00:13:45,817 --> 00:13:48,035
I'm going to be the one to expose them.

219
00:13:48,127 --> 00:13:50,057
No. I'll do it.

220
00:13:50,157 --> 00:13:52,802
We have to show them
what public opinion is.

221
00:13:53,097 --> 00:13:54,833
It's not NTS but our company.

222
00:13:55,287 --> 00:13:58,745
These are the texts between Ms Song and
our second major shareholder, Park Rosa.

223
00:14:00,768 --> 00:14:02,114
-What?
-Really?

224
00:14:02,357 --> 00:14:05,573
Yes. The chief mentioned in the texts
are the current Director Yeon Doo-young.

225
00:14:06,179 --> 00:14:09,461
They're our chief and director?

226
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:12,101
You should've said that sooner.

227
00:14:12,417 --> 00:14:14,684
Captain, you can report this, right?

228
00:14:14,977 --> 00:14:15,817
Right?

229
00:14:17,465 --> 00:14:18,962
Well, that's...

230
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:24,027
Hey, this is a different story.

231
00:14:24,127 --> 00:14:26,037
You have to go through the chief
and the director.

232
00:14:26,771 --> 00:14:28,514
There's no captain that can go through it.

233
00:14:29,546 --> 00:14:31,210
What if I give the information
over to YGN?

234
00:14:31,677 --> 00:14:33,727
It's worse because
it will be whistle-blowing.

235
00:14:33,827 --> 00:14:36,961
Once you're marked as a whistle-blower,
you can't work anywhere else.

236
00:14:37,537 --> 00:14:40,316
It will be the end of the reporter's life.

237
00:14:40,657 --> 00:14:42,275
Captain, you said it all the time.

238
00:14:42,366 --> 00:14:44,823
The blade of criticism has to be sharper
the higher you aim.

239
00:14:46,467 --> 00:14:50,617
Hey, but I can't be stabbed by that blade.

240
00:14:52,027 --> 00:14:56,200
My life would be on the line.
My kids are studying overseas.

241
00:14:56,847 --> 00:14:59,252
And it will be a while
until my kids go to college.

242
00:15:01,177 --> 00:15:02,683
I'm still renting.

243
00:15:03,183 --> 00:15:06,069
And there are 37 more
monthly payments left on my car.

244
00:15:07,217 --> 00:15:08,700
Captain. Il-joo.

245
00:15:10,337 --> 00:15:12,921
I'm too ashamed to look at you.

246
00:15:13,825 --> 00:15:15,077
But...

247
00:15:15,937 --> 00:15:18,105
Do you know when a dog gets eaten?

248
00:15:19,134 --> 00:15:21,525
It's when they don't recognize their owner
and bark at them.

249
00:15:22,677 --> 00:15:24,687
I know this is cowardly...

250
00:15:26,267 --> 00:15:30,400
but I don't want to be eaten yet.

251
00:15:33,185 --> 00:15:36,689
-Captain.
-Are you able to become a whistle-blower?

252
