Should we go get some tea?

283
00:18:22,507 --> 00:18:23,735
Sure.

284
00:18:32,398 --> 00:18:33,923
You're so strange today.

285
00:18:34,097 --> 00:18:35,537
What did you have to tell me?

286
00:18:37,194 --> 00:18:39,931
I came to give you an amazing exclusive.

287
00:18:40,022 --> 00:18:41,786
An exclusive? What is it?

288
00:18:44,797 --> 00:18:45,816
This is it.

289
00:18:48,566 --> 00:18:51,404
Why are you giving it to me?
Why don't you do it yourself?

290
00:18:51,798 --> 00:18:53,723
Because I can't do it, but you can.

291
00:18:59,427 --> 00:19:00,715
What is it?

292
00:19:04,548 --> 00:19:06,575
It's the cell phone that my mom
was using in 2000.

293
00:19:06,666 --> 00:19:10,526
And those are the restored
deleted text messages.

294
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:14,357
Take a look.

295
00:19:15,172 --> 00:19:17,747
Those are the text messages between
my mom and Bum-jo's mother.

296
00:19:20,809 --> 00:19:21,705
Bum-jo's mother?

297
00:19:25,238 --> 00:19:26,537
Restored Text MMS Messages

298
00:19:39,121 --> 00:19:41,967
I need somewhere
to avert the attention to.

299
00:19:42,613 --> 00:19:46,017
Highlight fireman Ki Ho-sang
in a negative light.

300
00:19:46,107 --> 00:19:47,863
Even his family if you need to...

301
00:19:47,954 --> 00:19:50,767
You're saying your father isn't at blame?
