00:26:27,162 --> 00:26:31,757
how these few texts changed
the truth of the case and shook the world.

376
00:26:37,744 --> 00:26:38,584
Ms Choi In-ha.

377
00:26:42,548 --> 00:26:45,962
Congratulations.
Director Yeon just notified the HR team.

378
00:26:46,053 --> 00:26:48,142
You are now a permanent employee.

379
00:26:51,874 --> 00:26:54,717
He started to the appeasement process
to prevent whistle-blowing.

380
00:26:55,599 --> 00:26:59,503
So forget about whistle-blowing
and report about other things.

381
00:27:00,239 --> 00:27:03,103
There are a lot of things to report
in the world other than whistle-blowing.

382
00:27:09,767 --> 00:27:10,700
What is this?

383
00:27:12,024 --> 00:27:12,964
It's my resignation letter.

384
00:27:16,650 --> 00:27:17,884
Thank you for everything.

385
00:27:25,957 --> 00:27:26,797
Why?

386
00:27:27,546 --> 00:27:29,583
I just told you that you became
a permanent employee.

387
00:27:29,674 --> 00:27:31,186
A permanent employee!

388
00:27:31,277 --> 00:27:33,177
A permanent employee
that can receive all four insurances.

389
00:27:35,777 --> 00:27:36,617
Follow me.

390
00:27:40,985 --> 00:27:43,104
What are you doing?
Didn't you hear just now?

391
00:27:43,195 --> 00:27:45,776
-You're a permanent employee now.
-Yes, I heard.

392
00:27:45,867 --> 00:27:47,287
I was so excited.

393
00:27:47,939 --> 00:27:49,532
I almost asked
for my resignation letter back.

394
00:27:50,250 --> 00:27:52,447
Are you saying that you'll hand that
over to YGN?

395
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:55,897
-You'll really be a whistle-blower?
-I already am.

396
00:27:56,037 --> 00:27:57,267
What?

397
00:27:57,564 --> 00:27:59,857
I already handed the files
over to YGN yesterday.

398
00:28:00,210 --> 00:28:01,478
That's why I submitted my resignation.

399
00:28:02,787 --> 00:28:04,596
Are you crazy? Just why?

400
00:28:04,687 --> 00:28:06,677
So that I could make the decision
without regrets.

401
00:28:07,816 --> 00:28:09,559
I think it's the right decision.

402
00:28:09,650 --> 00:28:11,346
Just why do you have to go this far?

403
00:28:11,809 --> 00:28:14,433
-Why don't you listen to me!
-I'm trying to apologize instead of you.

404
00:28:14,524 --> 00:28:15,744
What?

405
00:28:16,202 --> 00:28:17,887
Mom, you should've done this then.

406
00:28:18,306 --> 00:28:21,217
But you didn't do it and you aren't now,
so I'm doing it instead.

407
00:28:21,651 --> 00:28:23,457
Why do you have to apologize for me?

408
00:28:27,002 --> 00:28:28,528
Because I'm your daughter.

409
00:28:35,169 --> 00:28:37,106
I promised myself so many times...

410
00:28:37,197 --> 00:28:38,805
to think of you as a stranger.

411
00:28:39,988 --> 00:28:41,277
Since you abandoned me already,

412
00:28:41,387 --> 00:28:43,467
I just have to let go
and that will be the end.

413
00:28:45,183 --> 00:28:46,737
But I just can't do it.

414
00:28:49,746 --> 00:28:51,427
I just have to let go of this hand.

415
00:28:54,393 --> 00:28:56,878
But I can't. Like a fool...

416
00:29:17,493 --> 00:29:18,847
Where are we going first today?

417
00:29:19,478 --> 00:29:21,222
We have to interview Chairwoman Park Rosa.

418
00:29:21,313 --> 00:29:24,281
We have to barge in without an appointment
so it might get a little rough.

419
00:29:24,372 --> 00:29:25,502
That's my specialty.

420
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,527
Captain wanted me to give this to you.

421
00:29:31,958 --> 00:29:33,141
Is this a hidden camera?

422
00:29:33,232 --> 00:29:35,619
We might have to put down
the cameras for the interview.

423
00:29:38,733 --> 00:29:40,317
Wow, you can't tell at all.

