Thanks, Grandpa.

508
00:36:26,937 --> 00:36:29,187
It's not a crime to say
what needs to be said.

509
00:36:30,047 --> 00:36:32,037
It's a crime to say
what you shouldn't say.

510
00:36:32,147 --> 00:36:37,827
So don't be so defeated

511
00:36:37,927 --> 00:36:39,882
and cheer up.

512
00:36:40,322 --> 00:36:41,687
You got it?

513
00:36:42,832 --> 00:36:44,052
Grandpa...

514
00:36:44,143 --> 00:36:47,264
I heard everything from your dad.

515
00:36:47,355 --> 00:36:50,431
You did well, In-ha.

516
00:36:52,518 --> 00:36:56,177
-My baby... Yes. Yes.
-Thank you, Grandpa.

517
00:37:00,807 --> 00:37:02,707
Did you know about the relationship

518
00:37:02,807 --> 00:37:04,930
between Assemblyman
and Chairwoman Park Rosa?

519
00:37:05,021 --> 00:37:06,985
I'm not sure. I don't know.

520
00:37:07,076 --> 00:37:08,506
In-ha!

521
00:37:08,597 --> 00:37:10,437
Just sit still.
I can't focus because of you.

522
00:37:10,597 --> 00:37:13,667
-Be careful!
-Be quiet!

523
00:37:13,767 --> 00:37:16,067
-Hey, you need to watch out!
-Just stay still.

524
00:37:16,167 --> 00:37:17,317
Reporter Song Cha-ok.

525
00:37:17,407 --> 00:37:19,087
Factory Explosion Cause and casualty

526
00:37:22,767 --> 00:37:23,795
Hey!

527
00:37:23,886 --> 00:37:25,278
If they are to go stronger...

528
00:37:30,245 --> 00:37:32,012
Letter of Resignation
I couldn't say what I wanted to.

529
00:37:37,832 --> 00:37:39,104
Whose resignation is this?

530
00:37:40,670 --> 00:37:41,762
It's Choi In-ha's.

531
00:37:42,247 --> 00:37:44,982
Choi In-ha resigned? Why?

532
00:37:45,073 --> 00:37:47,471
She didn't want to be mistreated
because of whistle-blowing.

533
00:37:49,385 --> 00:37:50,913
She submitted this and left.

534
00:37:51,004 --> 00:37:54,813
Is it because of the report
she gave to us?

535
00:37:54,904 --> 00:37:57,588
Yes. I tried to stop her
but she wouldn't listen to me.

536
00:38:01,257 --> 00:38:04,108
Are you really going to report it?

537
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:06,701
Did you accept that resignation yet?

538
00:38:07,414 --> 00:38:08,570
I haven't yet.

539
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:15,793
I got goose bumps all over me.

540
00:38:16,057 --> 00:38:20,097
I matched the date of the texts
with the news reports from MSC.

541
00:38:20,286 --> 00:38:22,604
Yoon Yoo-Rae. That's pretty good.

542
00:38:24,107 --> 00:38:25,041
Captain!

543
00:38:25,267 --> 00:38:28,668
I organized the direction of reporting
after the texts into charts.

544
00:38:28,759 --> 00:38:30,977
-If we request for CGI..
-That's enough.

545
00:38:31,077 --> 00:38:32,552
Put a hold on making the connections
for now.

546
00:38:34,417 --> 00:38:35,585
Why?

547
00:38:36,602 --> 00:38:37,820
Ki Ha-myung. I want to see you.

548
00:38:38,637 --> 00:38:39,539
Yes.

549
00:38:42,457 --> 00:38:44,165
Why is Captain like that?

550
00:38:44,256 --> 00:38:46,337
Why does he keep changing his mind?

551
00:38:46,437 --> 00:38:47,792
It's so irritating.

552
00:38:51,191 --> 00:38:52,437
I'm sorry.

553
00:38:52,887 --> 00:38:55,637
-I got mad without realizing...
-I understand.

554
00:38:56,147 --> 00:38:58,334
I completely understand how you feel.

555
00:39:00,673 --> 00:39:04,241
Do you want to join me
on the path of a Nitpicker?

556
00:39:10,517 --> 00:39:12,199
The content of those texts,

557
00:39:12,577 --> 00:39:15,368
you said you got them
from Choi In-ha, right?

558
00:39:15,927 --> 00:39:18,953
Yes. I even received a request
from her asking me to report it.

559
00:39:19,044 --> 00:39:20,891
Did you check to see if she's okay?

560
00:39:22,027 --> 00:39:23,494
This is whistle-blowing.

561
00:39:23,797 --> 00:39:24,878
Whistle-blowing?

562
00:39:25,979 --> 00:39:30,027
It's criticizing the chief, director,
and major shareholder of her own company.

563
00:39:30,251 --> 00:39:33,907
The fact that she gave this to us means
she's prepared to quit.

564
00:39:34,107 --> 00:39:35,096
Did you not know?

565
00:39:36,997 --> 00:39:40,997
I had a lot to worry about,
but they all disappeared when I saw you.

566
00:39:44,087 --> 00:39:45,358
I didn't know.

567
00:39:48,230 --> 00:39:53,810
I confirmed with her captain today.
She submitted her resignation letter.

568
00:39:54,832 --> 00:39:55,697
A resignation letter?

569
00:39:55,956 --> 00:39:58,953
Go see her find out she's really alright.

570
00:39:59,937 --> 00:40:03,186
You have to put your life on the line
when whistle-blowing.

571
00:40:03,337 --> 00:40:07,284
You have to be ready to lose your company,
your colleague and even your future.

572
00:40:10,104 --> 00:40:12,224
Don't think that it's simply reasonable.

573
00:40:17,337 --> 00:40:19,417
-Ki Ha-myung.
-Yes.

574
00:40:19,517 --> 00:40:23,306
I know how angry you must've been
because of this connection.

575
00:40:24,727 --> 00:40:27,819
And I know that you want to satisfy
your grudge through this report.

576
00:40:28,574 --> 00:40:30,671
But don't be so blinded
by satisfying your grudge

577
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:34,013
that you forget about the things
you must think about as a reporter.

578
00:40:36,029 --> 00:40:37,242
Yes, Captain.

579
00:40:37,891 --> 00:40:39,460
I'll be out for a little while.

580
00:40:45,970 --> 00:40:47,977
Choi In-ha, where are you?

581
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:51,907
I stayed up all night making this.

582
00:40:52,194 --> 00:40:53,623
He didn't even acknowledge it...

583
00:41:08,629 --> 00:41:09,887
This is...

584
00:41:15,087 --> 00:41:16,139
Let me drink this.

585
00:41:20,904 --> 00:41:24,359
Hey, Captain just flirted with me, right?

586
00:41:24,450 --> 00:41:26,440
What are you talking about? What flirting?

587
00:41:26,531 --> 00:41:29,591
He stole my drink from me that time.
This is the same drink from that time.

588
00:41:31,737 --> 00:41:32,947
So?

589
00:41:33,047 --> 00:41:35,809
He remembered that he stole it
from me that time and bought me this.

590
00:41:36,027 --> 00:41:37,160
It's 100 percent flirting.

591
00:41:38,433 --> 00:41:40,149
Don't you think he's amazingly detailed?

592
00:41:42,221 --> 00:41:45,267
Or did he steal my drink intentionally?

593
00:41:45,367 --> 00:41:46,722
To kiss me indirectly?

594
00:41:48,247 --> 00:41:50,217
Then...

595
00:41:51,172 --> 00:41:52,383
Did the Captain flirt with me too?

596
00:41:53,187 --> 00:41:55,847
-You got one too?
-Yeah.

597
00:41:57,342 --> 00:41:58,557
Really?

598
00:41:59,421 --> 00:42:01,627
-Then am I the only who is strange?
-Yeah.

599
00:42:01,727 --> 00:42:04,492
You're the only one who's strange.
You're really strange.

600
00:42:05,559 --> 00:42:06,806
Go see a doctor.

601
00:42:09,687 --> 00:42:11,067
I guess...

602
00:42:12,484 --> 00:42:15,077
Even when I think about it,
I think I'm a little narcissistic.

603
00:42:15,827 --> 00:42:18,607
Even though I was taken advantage of,
here I go again.

604
00:42:33,540 --> 00:42:36,542
For a beginner,
wasn't my driving pretty great?

605
00:42:38,002 --> 00:42:42,268
It's not great, but it's crazy.

606
00:42:42,359 --> 00:42:44,907
Every time you had to turn left,
you made a u-turn...

607
00:42:45,007 --> 00:42:47,667
Wow, it'll only be a matter time
until I make Chan-soo

608
00:42:47,767 --> 00:42:50,023
a single dad, if I keep giving you
driving lessons.

609
00:42:52,737 --> 00:42:53,821
Choi In-ha.

610
00:42:54,227 --> 00:42:56,297
-You're here.
-You came, my friend?

611
00:42:56,397 --> 00:42:58,917
-You're here.
-Come out and talk with me.

612
00:42:59,237 --> 00:43:02,307
-What is it about? Talk to me here.
-Hey, you!

613
00:43:02,417 --> 00:43:04,347
Okay, I'm coming out.

614
00:43:05,427 --> 00:43:08,017
Teach me tomorrow too.
Chan-soo, I'll come by again next time.

615
00:43:18,326 --> 00:43:20,026
Why didn't you tell me
about the resignation letter?

616
00:43:21,227 --> 00:43:24,347
Look at yourself. I knew that
you would just get mad for no reason.

617
00:43:24,447 --> 00:43:26,083
You think that I'm getting mad
without reason?

618
00:43:26,718 --> 00:43:29,404
No. I know that you're mad
because you're worried about me.

619
00:43:29,495 --> 00:43:32,375
I know what you're going to say too.
But I'm completely fine.

620
00:43:32,828 --> 00:43:35,927
I'm practicing driving
and I'm taking English classes too.

621
00:43:36,313 --> 00:43:39,077
I'll be submitting my resumes again
starting tomorrow.

622
00:43:39,642 --> 00:43:42,638
Your resignation hasn't been processed yet
so hurry up and return to your company.

623
00:43:43,767 --> 00:43:44,882
I don't want to.

624
00:43:48,117 --> 00:43:51,173
I'm going to pretend that
I didn't receive those texts from you.

625
00:43:52,737 --> 00:43:53,694
What?

626
00:43:54,582 --> 00:43:56,119
You won't report them?

627
00:43:56,210 --> 00:43:57,240
No.

628
00:43:58,159 --> 00:44:01,347
I must've heard you wrong.
If not, you must've gone crazy.

629
00:44:01,447 --> 00:44:03,841
Don't you know what I was feeling
when I gave it to you?

630
00:44:03,932 --> 00:44:04,874
I didn't know.

631
00:44:04,965 --> 00:44:07,517
I was so focused on revealing
what happened 14 years ago

632
00:44:07,637 --> 00:44:09,727
that I didn't realize
that it was whistle-blowing,

633
00:44:09,817 --> 00:44:11,607
or what would happen to you.

634
00:44:11,747 --> 00:44:14,080
If I knew that you gave up on
being a reporter to give me the report...

635
00:44:14,687 --> 00:44:15,808
I wouldn't have accepted it.

636
00:44:16,997 --> 00:44:18,357
Are you crazy?

637
00:44:18,578 --> 00:44:22,014
With that you can reveal to the world
how unjustly your family was destroyed.

638
00:44:22,105 --> 00:44:23,243
So why would you give up on it?

639
00:44:26,217 --> 00:44:29,487
If you were me,
would you accept this report?

640
00:44:30,100 --> 00:44:31,967
Even if my life would be ruined?

641
00:44:32,067 --> 00:44:33,263
Could you really do it?

642
00:44:41,545 --> 00:44:42,667
Answer me.

643
00:44:43,157 --> 00:44:44,766
I'll do it according to your answer.

644
00:44:46,437 --> 00:44:47,737
Yeah.

645
00:44:47,827 --> 00:44:48,955
I can do it.

646
00:44:49,898 --> 00:44:52,637
Whatever happens to your life,
I would've accepted that report.

647
00:44:59,837 --> 00:45:01,397
See?

648
00:45:01,924 --> 00:45:03,247
You can't do it either.

649
00:45:04,256 --> 00:45:06,423
Why are you telling me to do something
that you can't do yourself?

650
00:45:07,337 --> 00:45:08,880
Then you answer me too.

651
00:45:09,875 --> 00:45:11,837
What would you do if you were me?

652
00:45:12,666 --> 00:45:13,721
Would you just bury this?

653
00:45:17,987 --> 00:45:19,457
No.

654
00:45:19,557 --> 00:45:20,750
I won't bury it.

655
00:45:21,575 --> 00:45:23,567
I'm going to do whatever
it takes to reveal the connections

656
00:45:23,677 --> 00:45:25,010
using other ways than using your report.

657
00:45:26,847 --> 00:45:28,887
What other way?

658
00:45:28,997 --> 00:45:32,182
-What other way is there than this?
-There is.

659
00:45:32,273 --> 00:45:35,413
Of course it will take longer
and it will be hard but there is a way.

660
00:45:36,453 --> 00:45:38,055
So return to your company for now.

661
00:45:39,051 --> 00:45:40,629
Let's look for another way together.

662
00:45:45,307 --> 00:45:46,758
But it's such a waste.

663
00:45:48,168 --> 00:45:50,239
We can reveal it all with this.

664
00:45:57,522 --> 00:45:58,955
I'm not saying that I won't do it.

665
00:45:59,827 --> 00:46:01,567
I'm just saying that
I'm going to find another way.

666
00:46:20,304 --> 00:46:23,031
I found out while I was talking to my mom
about the texts.

667
00:46:23,206 --> 00:46:27,231
She tried to be a whistle-blower
on connection 14 years ago too.

668
00:46:27,957 --> 00:46:30,629
But because of the threat
of getting fired...

669
00:46:31,299 --> 00:46:33,600
...she went along
with Bum-jo's mother's appeasement.

670
00:46:33,691 --> 00:46:38,154
This is Song Cha-ok,
a promising reporter of MSC.

671
00:46:38,377 --> 00:46:40,224
She's a talented reporter.

672
00:46:40,767 --> 00:46:41,932
It's nice to meet you.

673
00:46:45,784 --> 00:46:47,191
I think that was when she started...

674
00:46:48,607 --> 00:46:50,728
to be a blower for Bum-jo's mother.

675
00:46:50,977 --> 00:46:54,497
It seems like after she made that decision
she started to get continual success.

676
00:46:55,178 --> 00:46:57,596
The first female reporter captain
and special correspondent.

677
00:46:57,687 --> 00:46:59,083
And even the youngest chief.

678
00:46:59,817 --> 00:47:01,289
Don't you think it's incredible?

679
00:47:04,167 --> 00:47:05,125
Yeah.

680
00:47:06,920 --> 00:47:09,041
But I didn't want to make
the same decision that my mom made.

681
00:47:10,087 --> 00:47:11,966
That's why handed the texts over to you.

682
00:47:12,727 --> 00:47:13,877
I know.

683
00:47:15,999 --> 00:47:18,141
But truth be told, I was scared.

684
00:47:19,163 --> 00:47:23,981
My dad was the opposite of my mom.
His life was ruined by whistle-blowing.

685
00:47:25,981 --> 00:47:28,447
-Your dad?
-Yeah.

686
00:47:29,125 --> 00:47:32,627
My dad used to be
a successful bank manager.

687
00:47:33,857 --> 00:47:35,217
Your dad?

688
00:47:38,180 --> 00:47:40,287
Yes. This is Choi Dal-pyung
from Loans Department.

689
00:47:40,387 --> 00:47:41,717
Yes.

690
00:47:41,817 --> 00:47:44,277
Loan consultation?

691
00:47:45,146 --> 00:47:48,757
Yes, it's possible.
Please visit us. Thank you.

692
00:47:50,657 --> 00:47:53,207
I can't believe it either but it was true.

693
00:47:56,397 --> 00:47:57,963
But what did he report?

694
00:47:58,207 --> 00:48:01,597
He reported the bank president's
illegal loans to the newspaper.

695
00:48:02,467 --> 00:48:04,737
Because of that report,
the bank president was fired

696
00:48:04,837 --> 00:48:06,619
and the loan corruption decreased. But...

697
00:48:06,710 --> 00:48:09,510
I knew it since he started to brag
about being the youngest manager.

698
00:48:09,687 --> 00:48:11,449
Everyone should watch their words
around him.

699
00:48:11,540 --> 00:48:13,630
Hello. Good morning.

700
00:48:14,977 --> 00:48:16,047
Let's go.

701
00:48:19,718 --> 00:48:21,977
I think his work life became
really difficult.

702
00:48:22,622 --> 00:48:25,367
Everyone stopped talking in front of him
and they didn't eat together with him.

703
00:48:25,812 --> 00:48:27,667
He said he felt like
he was an invisible man.

704
00:48:29,257 --> 00:48:33,752
In the end, he thought that it wasn't
a job but a waste of life, so he quit.

705
00:48:34,564 --> 00:48:37,817
But he was marked as a whistle-blower,
so it was difficult getting a new job.

706
00:48:37,917 --> 00:48:41,747
And IMF crisis happened,
so he was forced to stay jobless.

707
00:48:42,032 --> 00:48:44,650
He was in conflict over that with my mom
and ended up getting a divorce.

708
00:48:46,297 --> 00:48:47,917
I see.

709
00:48:49,717 --> 00:48:50,896
But I'm curious.

710
00:48:51,977 --> 00:48:52,888
About what?

711
00:48:53,537 --> 00:48:56,627
Whether the two of them
regret their decisions.

712
00:49:00,797 --> 00:49:03,010
I know. I'm getting curious too.

713
00:49:12,859 --> 00:49:16,287
Recently my son wanted
to slowly start studying business,

714
00:49:16,841 --> 00:49:19,339
so he quit being a reporter
and is traveling with me.

715
00:49:22,407 --> 00:49:23,627
How do you find the painting?

716
00:49:23,727 --> 00:49:25,567
I  heard Assemblyman Shin's wife
painted these.

717
00:49:25,667 --> 00:49:28,087
I'm not sure.
I don't know much about paintings.

718
00:49:28,187 --> 00:49:30,007
I don't either.

719
00:49:30,474 --> 00:49:32,364
They all seem like a waste of paint.

720
00:49:36,722 --> 00:49:38,621
The purpose of these exhibitions
is obvious.

721
00:49:39,214 --> 00:49:42,523
They're saying that someone like me should
open up their wallet, so what can I do?

722
00:49:42,614 --> 00:49:44,571
I have to go along with
what the Assemblymen want.

723
00:49:45,306 --> 00:49:46,747
Would this be enough?

724
00:49:51,808 --> 00:49:54,656
If our Assemblymen hold exhibitions,
I buy paintings.

725
00:49:54,747 --> 00:49:57,934
If they hold a publication party,
we give congratulatory money.

726
00:49:58,663 --> 00:50:01,647
If there's a problem,
we use the news to keep it covered.

727
00:50:03,898 --> 00:50:07,451
Ms Song, you know how much I did
for those Assemblymen too, right?

728
00:50:08,184 --> 00:50:09,326
Yes, ma'am.

729
00:50:09,417 --> 00:50:13,077
But all that hard work is being shaken,
so I'm a little worried.

730
00:50:13,937 --> 00:50:18,112
These days you have to be careful
about trivial gossip even.

731
00:50:19,636 --> 00:50:22,132
A little while ago, was it Ki Ha-myung?

732
00:50:22,223 --> 00:50:24,581
That guy even brought the camera crew

733
00:50:24,971 --> 00:50:27,097
and asked about what happened
14 years ago.

734
00:50:27,327 --> 00:50:28,467
Yes.

735
00:50:28,567 --> 00:50:31,187
Since he's not from our side,
he'll be difficult to appease.

736
00:50:31,790 --> 00:50:34,287
He didn't even seem like the kind
you can easily persuade.

737
00:50:35,424 --> 00:50:36,737
That's why I'm saying this.

738
00:50:38,786 --> 00:50:40,327
Your daughter...

739
00:50:42,497 --> 00:50:43,657
Choi In-ha.

740
00:50:44,473 --> 00:50:46,977
Can you arrange a meeting with her?

741
00:50:50,234 --> 00:50:51,435
Why do you want to meet my daughter?

742
00:50:53,707 --> 00:50:56,447
You know that she is very close
with Ki Ha-myung, right?

743
00:50:57,347 --> 00:51:00,517
I think it might be easier to target her.

744
00:51:01,614 --> 00:51:02,497
Ma'am.

745
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:08,247
Don't worry. I won't treat her badly.

746
00:51:08,639 --> 00:51:09,997
You know me.

747
00:51:10,406 --> 00:51:13,307
I only make good suggestions
that you can't refuse.

748
00:51:13,844 --> 00:51:16,614
I treated you so well 14 years ago too.

749
00:51:19,973 --> 00:51:24,094
I just want to make another
good relationship, like the one we have.

750
00:51:25,284 --> 00:51:26,747
You understand what I mean, don't you?

751
00:51:30,027 --> 00:51:31,577
Yes.

752
00:51:39,117 --> 00:51:41,647
I didn't know that you'd wear
those rotten sweats again.

753
00:51:42,778 --> 00:51:46,248
I'm going to rip it up or burn it
next time I do laundry.

754
00:51:46,339 --> 00:51:48,106
What? It's perfectly fine.

755
00:51:50,955 --> 00:51:51,940
But I'm curious.

756
00:51:52,625 --> 00:51:53,855
About what?

757
00:51:54,174 --> 00:51:57,055
Whether the two of them
regret their decisions.

758
00:51:58,825 --> 00:52:00,135
Dad.

759
00:52:01,384 --> 00:52:03,668
Don't you regret reporting
the bank president?

760
00:52:04,063 --> 00:52:05,256
No, I don't regret.

761
00:52:06,216 --> 00:52:09,554
If I didn't do it and hold it in,
I would've died of repressed anger.

762
00:52:10,402 --> 00:52:14,069
So you would've made the same decision
even if you went back to the past?

763
00:52:14,545 --> 00:52:16,685
No. I wouldn't make the same decision.

764
00:52:18,111 --> 00:52:19,785
What? I thought you didn't regret?

765
00:52:22,206 --> 00:52:23,538
I do regret.

766
00:52:23,629 --> 00:52:26,029
After I quit,
I was jobless for over 10 years.

767
00:52:26,933 --> 00:52:29,455
Then you don't want to report it
and live like mom?

768
00:52:29,546 --> 00:52:32,345
-Is that right?
-No. I would hate that even more.

769
00:52:33,203 --> 00:52:35,722
Then what is it? What are you regretting?

770
00:52:37,085 --> 00:52:40,975
I should not have quit and endured longer.
That kind of regret...

771
00:52:45,107 --> 00:52:46,665
Although they were nasty and
petty toward me,

772
00:52:46,765 --> 00:52:49,365
I should've endured in the company.

773
00:52:49,726 --> 00:52:53,096
I regret most about giving up so easily
and leaving.

774
00:53:21,705 --> 00:53:23,491
Are you going to practice driving?

775
00:53:23,745 --> 00:53:24,825
No.

776
00:53:25,628 --> 00:53:27,124
I'm going to the company.

777
00:53:31,335 --> 00:53:32,562
The company?

778
00:53:36,107 --> 00:53:39,707
My mom tried to be a whistle-blower
because of that connection 14 years ago.

779
00:53:54,075 --> 00:53:55,355
Choi In-ha.

780
00:53:57,677 --> 00:53:58,955
-Did you decide to return?
-Yeah.

781
00:53:59,055 --> 00:54:01,348
I called the captain, he told me to come.

782
00:54:01,439 --> 00:54:03,118
So I'm going to try to endure
no matter what.

783
00:54:03,209 --> 00:54:06,442
Just like you said, I think
I'll have to look for a way inside there.

784
00:54:11,855 --> 00:54:13,055
Cheers.

785
00:54:15,715 --> 00:54:16,865
Cheers.

786
00:54:22,897 --> 00:54:25,427
You need to go over there.
This is my company.

787
00:54:27,476 --> 00:54:29,435
I have a business over here too.
Let's go.

788
00:54:35,374 --> 00:54:39,574
I just want to make another
good relationship like the one we have.

789
00:54:40,718 --> 00:54:42,076
You understand what I mean, don't you?

790
00:54:59,795 --> 00:55:01,005
Reporter Song.

791
00:55:02,578 --> 00:55:03,804
I have something to tell you.

792
00:55:03,895 --> 00:55:05,545
Please let me have a brief moment.

793
00:55:14,249 --> 00:55:17,551
-What is this?
-The texts I received from In-ha.

794
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:19,545
The cell phone is inside too.

795
00:55:21,768 --> 00:55:23,487
I'll pretend that I didn't receive them.

796
00:55:23,578 --> 00:55:26,256
If I do this,
In-ha didn't blow the whistle.

797
00:55:26,671 --> 00:55:30,099
So I hope there won't be any
negative results for In-ha because of it.

798
00:55:32,505 --> 00:55:33,605
Why are you doing this?

799
00:55:34,313 --> 00:55:36,472
-Don't you know what this is?
-I know.

800
00:55:36,899 --> 00:55:40,236
Those are the files
that can reveal the people

801
00:55:40,327 --> 00:55:41,675
who framed my father 14 years ago.

802
00:55:42,262 --> 00:55:45,217
These files can also
bring you down as well.

803
00:55:46,153 --> 00:55:47,302
So why are you doing this?

804
00:55:48,146 --> 00:55:50,962
I thought you desperately wanted these.

805
00:55:51,053 --> 00:55:54,151
Yes. I do want it desperately.

806
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,022
It's my wish to report this to the world.

807
00:55:57,463 --> 00:56:00,272
But I can't ruin someone else's life,

808
00:56:00,363 --> 00:56:02,253
because of that wish and greed.

809
00:56:04,098 --> 00:56:06,096
Is that why you're giving up
on reporting this?

810
00:56:07,755 --> 00:56:09,015
No.

811
00:56:10,239 --> 00:56:13,210
I'm asking you to report it.

812
00:56:19,325 --> 00:56:21,725
I heard that you gave up
on blowing the whistle

813
00:56:21,816 --> 00:56:24,187
and accepted Chairwoman Park's
appeasement 14 years ago.

814
00:56:24,659 --> 00:56:26,282
And because of that decision...

815
00:56:28,260 --> 00:56:29,755
my family was horribly destroyed.

816
00:56:32,235 --> 00:56:33,915
In-ha doesn't have the power
to report that.

817
00:56:34,410 --> 00:56:37,056
But if I report it,
In-ha will be hurt too.

818
00:56:39,165 --> 00:56:40,095
So?

819
00:56:40,569 --> 00:56:43,700
The person responsible for that tragedy
is not In-ha, but you.

820
00:56:43,791 --> 00:56:47,122
So you have to be the one
to reveal this to the world.

821
00:56:51,941 --> 00:56:56,006
Do you think that I would report this
for that reason?

822
00:56:56,745 --> 00:56:58,476
So you're handing these over to me?

823
00:56:59,979 --> 00:57:01,650
Aren't you too naive?

824
00:57:01,741 --> 00:57:05,302
Yes. I know that
this is a ridiculous gamble.

825
00:57:06,041 --> 00:57:07,525
But I want to believe in my craziness.

826
00:57:08,374 --> 00:57:09,815
There was a moment...

827
00:57:10,253 --> 00:57:12,190
that you were determined to
become a whistle-blower.

828
00:57:12,960 --> 00:57:14,174
You were once a reporter.

829
00:57:14,265 --> 00:57:17,380
And maybe you might regret the decision
you made 14 years ago.

830
00:57:17,918 --> 00:57:19,871
I wanted to naively believe in that.

831
00:57:24,465 --> 00:57:25,596
I'm asking you.

832
00:57:26,224 --> 00:57:29,785
Please report it yourself.

833
00:57:34,805 --> 00:57:38,345
In-ha and also you, Ki Ha-myung...

834
00:57:40,520 --> 00:57:42,702
You both are so reckless
to the point that I'm irritated.

835
00:58:01,394 --> 00:58:03,212
Why should you be sorry?

836
00:58:03,833 --> 00:58:05,859
Because my mom is not apologizing
or correcting it.

837
00:58:07,283 --> 00:58:10,671
Why don't the people believe you
even when you're telling the truth?

838
00:58:11,023 --> 00:58:13,439
They're whining so much
that I'm really irritated.

839
00:58:14,505 --> 00:58:15,427
You're a fraud.

840
00:58:16,393 --> 00:58:18,025
You abandoned me anyway.

841
00:58:18,450 --> 00:58:21,578
President Joo Sang-ho. You fabricated
this death certificate, right?

842
00:58:21,669 --> 00:58:23,756
Our relationship will end
if I just let it go.

843
00:58:24,926 --> 00:58:26,223
But I just can't do it.

844
00:58:26,314 --> 00:58:29,150
Why couldn't you even believe in yourself?

845
00:58:31,299 --> 00:58:33,423
I'm stressed to the point of irritation.

846
00:58:34,320 --> 00:58:37,065
-Are you even a reporter?
-I just need to let go of this hand.

847
00:58:41,081 --> 00:58:43,663
But I just can't. Like a fool.

848
00:58:47,816 --> 00:58:50,701
Embarrassing me to the point
that I'm irritated.

849
00:59:16,666 --> 00:59:18,306
When will I be able to see Choi In-ha?

850
00:59:18,397 --> 00:59:21,176
Could it be a warning?
To watch your mouth.

851
00:59:21,267 --> 00:59:23,747
I have an informant.
I wonder if we were too reckless.

852
00:59:23,838 --> 00:59:25,441
Dig up without the director knowing.

853
00:59:25,532 --> 00:59:29,940
It's so annoying to have bugs in my farms
that I've worked on for 20 years!

854
00:59:30,031 --> 00:59:32,021
I'm going to give the report.
Just cover it properly.

855
00:59:32,112 --> 00:59:33,988
Now that I think about it,
this is a first.

856
00:59:34,079 --> 00:59:36,582
That you added a condition on my request.

857
00:59:36,673 --> 00:59:40,713
I dreamt that Dal-Po asked me
for permission to date In-ha.
